PageDisplayTitle:Aesthenosphere
PageDescription:The Layer that the Crust Floats on
SubtopicName:Layers

The Aesthenosphere is the layer just below the crust, part of the mantle. There is not enough pressure to turn it solid, so the tectonic plates of the crust can float on it.

